On August 27, 2018, President Donald J. Trump issued a proclamation to honor the memory and service of Senator John Sidney McCain III. The proclamation orders that the flag of the United States be flown at half-staff at the White House, public buildings and grounds, military posts, naval stations, naval vessels, and all other federal government facilities in the District of Columbia and throughout the United States and its territories and possessions until sunset on the day of interment. It also directs that the flag be flown at half-staff for the same period at all United States embassies, legations, consular offices, and other facilities abroad, including military facilities and naval vessels and stations. The proclamation was signed by President Trump on August 27, 2018.